<module>
    <h>geal</h>
    <p><g>geal</g>
        <en>white</en> is a <a href="?xx=adjectives/simple_adjectives">simple adjective</a>.</p>

    <section>
        <h>nouns</h>
        <module id="taigh">
            <h>taigh</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=taigh">taigh</a> geal</g>
                <en>a white house</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Cha b’ann geal a bha an taigh.</gd>
                        <tr>The house was not white.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 33</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </module>
        <module id="tubhailte">
            <h>tubhailte</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=tubhailte">tubhailte</a> gheal</g>
                <en>a white tablecloth</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>An ann geal a tha an tubhailte seo? Chan ann. Dé an dath a tha air an
                            tubhailte? Tha dath gorm.</gd>
                        <tr>Is this tablecloth white? No, it isn’t. What colour is the tablecloth?
                            It is blue.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 35</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </module>
        <module id="dath">
            <h>dath</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=dath">dath</a> geal</g> <en>[the] colour white</en> – <xl>
                <li>
                    <gd>An ann geal a tha an tubhailte seo? Chan ann. Dé an dath a tha air an
                        tubhailte? Tha dath gorm. Alasdair, an e dath gorm a tha air an tubhailte? ’S e.</gd>
                    <tr>Is this tablecloth white? No, it isn’t. What colour is the tablecloth?
                        It is blue. Alexander – is the colour of the tablecloth blue? Yes, it is.</tr>
                    <ref text="617">td. 35</ref>
                </li>
            </xl>
            </p>
        </module>
    </section>

